text: Garrard County is a county in the U.S. state of Kentucky. As of the 2020 U. S. Census, the population was 16,953. Its county seat is Lancaster. The county was formed on December 17, 1796 and was named for James Garrard, who was Governor of Kentucky from 1796 to 1804. == References == Category:1790s establishments in Kentucky Category:1796 establishments in the United States Category:Kentucky counties
